  "prompt": "What is kale called in Hindi or Marathi?",
  "response": "In Hindi, kale is commonly referred to as \"\u0915\u093e\u0932\u0947 \u091a\u0928\u0947\" (kale chane) or \"\u0938\u093e\u0917\" (saag) for leafy greens in general. However, if you are specifically asking about the variety of kale (the leafy green vegetable), it may just be referred to as \"\u0915\u0947\u0932\" (kel). \n\nIn Marathi, kale is also called \"\u0915\u0947\u0932\" (kel), and similarly to Hindi, it is sometimes grouped under the broader category of leafy greens.\n\nKeep in mind that kale may not be as commonly used in Indian cuisines as it is in Western diets, so it may not have a widely recognized traditional name in either language.",
